sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant Konflux as Konflux Build System
    participant Cachi2 as cachi2 Prefetch
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>(registry.redhat.io / quay.io)
    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(Envoy) 443/TCP
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Nginx as nginx (Code-Server)<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant CS as code-server<br/>8787/TCP HTTP
    participant Httpd as httpd CGI<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DSPA as Data Science Pipelines<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Runtime as Runtime Image<br/>(Pipeline Pod)
    participant Culler as Notebook Controller<br/>Culler

    Note over Dev,Registry: Flow 1: Workbench Image Build (Konflux)
    Dev->>Konflux: Push code changes
    Konflux->>Cachi2: Prefetch dependencies<br/>(RPMs, pip, npm, generic)<br/>HTTPS/443
    Cachi2-->>Konflux: Cached artifacts<br/>(file mount)
    Konflux->>Konflux: Build Dockerfile.konflux.*<br/>(hermetic, network-isolated)
    Konflux->>Registry: Push container images<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+

    Note over Operator,Dashboard: ImageStream Deployment
    Operator->>Operator: Deploy ImageStream manifests<br/>from manifests/rhoai/base/
    Dashboard->>Operator: Read ImageStream annotations<br/>(via Kubernetes API)

    Note over User,CS: Flow 2: Workbench Launch (Jupyter)
    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench flavor
    Dashboard->>Operator: Create Notebook CR
    User->>Gateway: Access workbench<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>OAuth/OIDC
    Gateway->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+<br/>OAuth Token
    KRBP->>Jupyter: Proxy to JupyterLab<br/>HTTP/8888 (localhost)<br/>No auth (trusted sidecar)
    Jupyter-->>KRBP: JupyterLab response
    KRBP-->>Gateway: HTTPS response
    Gateway-->>User: Workbench UI

    Note over User,CS: Flow 2b: Workbench Launch (Code-Server)
    User->>Gateway: Access Code-Server workbench<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
    KRBP->>Nginx: Proxy to nginx<br/>HTTP/80 (localhost)
    Nginx->>CS: Forward to code-server<br/>HTTP/8787 (localhost)
    CS-->>Nginx: VS Code response
    Nginx-->>KRBP: Response
    KRBP-->>Gateway: HTTPS response
    Gateway-->>User: Code-Server UI

    Note over Jupyter,Runtime: Flow 3: Elyra Pipeline Submission
    User->>Jupyter: Design pipeline in Elyra
    Jupyter->>DSPA: Submit pipeline run<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    DSPA->>Runtime: Launch pipeline pod<br/>with runtime image
    Runtime->>Runtime: Execute pipeline step
    Runtime-->>DSPA: Step result

    Note over Culler,Httpd: Flow 4: Idle Culling (Code-Server)
    Culler->>KRBP: Poll /api/kernels/<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    KRBP->>Nginx: Forward to nginx<br/>HTTP/80
    Nginx->>Nginx: Check access log<br/>(JSON format)
    Culler->>Httpd: Poll CGI endpoint<br/>HTTP/8080
    Httpd->>CS: access.cgi checks<br/>/codeserver/healthz<br/>HTTP/8888
    CS-->>Httpd: Heartbeat response
    Httpd-->>Culler: Jupyter-compatible<br/>kernel format response
